mappings.name: Patch VM instances by creating and running a patch job.

schema.description: A high level representation of a patch job that is either in progress or has completed. Instance details are not included in the job. To paginate through instance details, use `ListPatchJobInstanceDetails`. For more information about patch jobs, see [Creating patch jobs](https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/os-patch-management/create-patch-job).

createTime.description: Time this patch job was created.

description.description: Description of the patch job. Length of the description is limited to 1024 characters.

displayName.description: Display name for this patch job. This is not a unique identifier.

dryRun.description: If this patch job is a dry run, the agent reports that it has finished without running any updates on the VM instance.

duration.description: Duration of the patch job. After the duration ends, the patch job times out.

errorMessage.description: If this patch job failed, this message provides information about the failure.

name.description: Unique identifier for this patch job in the form `projects/*/patchJobs/*`

patchDeployment.description: Output only. Name of the patch deployment that created this patch job.

percentComplete.description: Reflects the overall progress of the patch job in the range of 0.0 being no progress to 100.0 being complete.

state.description: The current state of the PatchJob.

updateTime.description: Last time this patch job was updated.

mappings.name: Get a list of patch jobs.

schema.description: A response message for listing patch jobs.

nextPageToken.description: A pagination token that can be used to get the next page of results.

mappings.name: Create an OS Config patch deployment.

schema.description: Patch deployments are configurations that individual patch jobs use to complete a patch. These configurations include instance filter, package repository settings, and a schedule. For more information about creating and managing patch deployments, see [Scheduling patch jobs](https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/os-patch-management/schedule-patch-jobs).

createTime.description: Output only. Time the patch deployment was created. Timestamp is in [RFC3339](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3339.txt) text format.

description.description: Optional. Description of the patch deployment. Length of the description is limited to 1024 characters.

duration.description: Optional. Duration of the patch. After the duration ends, the patch times out.

lastExecuteTime.description: Output only. The last time a patch job was started by this deployment. Timestamp is in [RFC3339](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3339.txt) text format.

name.description: Unique name for the patch deployment resource in a project. The patch deployment name is in the form: `projects/{project_id}/patchDeployments/{patch_deployment_id}`. This field is ignored when you create a new patch deployment.

state.description: Output only. Current state of the patch deployment.

updateTime.description: Output only. Time the patch deployment was last updated. Timestamp is in [RFC3339](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3339.txt) text format.

mappings.name: Get a page of OS Config patch deployments.

schema.description: A response message for listing patch deployments.

nextPageToken.description: A pagination token that can be used to get the next page of patch deployments.

mappings.name: Get a list of instance details for a given patch job.

schema.description: A response message for listing the instances details for a patch job.

nextPageToken.description: A pagination token that can be used to get the next page of results.

mappings.name: Create an OS Config guest policy.

schema.description: An OS Config resource representing a guest configuration policy. These policies represent the desired state for VM instance guest environments including packages to install or remove, package repository configurations, and software to install.

createTime.description: Output only. Time this guest policy was created.

description.description: Description of the guest policy. Length of the description is limited to 1024 characters.

etag.description: The etag for this guest policy. If this is provided on update, it must match the server's etag.

name.description: Required. Unique name of the resource in this project using one of the following forms: `projects/{project_number}/guestPolicies/{guest_policy_id}`.

packageRepositories.description: A list of package repositories to configure on the VM instance. This is done before any other configs are applied so they can use these repos. Package repositories are only configured if the corresponding package manager(s) are available.

packages.description: The software packages to be managed by this policy.

recipes.description: A list of Recipes to install on the VM instance.

updateTime.description: Output only. Last time this guest policy was updated.

mappings.name: Get a page of OS Config guest policies.

schema.description: A response message for listing guest policies.

nextPageToken.description: A pagination token that can be used to get the next page of guest policies.
